"{\"uid\": \"greekreporter.com-2024-08-01-google-olympic-ai-ad-backlash\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Google, one of the main sponsors of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games, has sparked criticism over their Olympic AI ad, created in support of Team USA.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9998481937848054, \"rank\": 0.0001518292615539078, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 136, \"end\": 144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999826497971, \"rank\": 8.254289776680493e-09, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The controversial Olympic AI ad is titled \\\"Dear Sydney,\\\" and it features a father using GoogleGeminito help his daughter write a letter to her favorite athlete, Sydney McLaughling-Levrone.\", \"from\": 147, \"to\": 335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 308, \"end\": 314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999886985492293, \"rank\": 9.750648790704081e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Google's ad has sparked criticism over the use of AI for something as personal as writing a letter.\", \"from\": 337, \"to\": 436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 337, \"end\": 343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9998481937848054, \"rank\": 0.0001518292615539078, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 387, \"end\": 389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 4.3677762977779635e-12, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Social media users have said Google is actively trying to replace human emotion with AI-generated content, such as the letter in the ad.\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 466, \"end\": 472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9998481937848054, \"rank\": 0.0001518292615539078, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Social media users were not the only ones who scrutinized Google's AI ad.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 633, \"end\": 639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9998481937848054, \"rank\": 0.0001518292615539078, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Academic voices have also added to the intense scrutiny ofGoogle.\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 714, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps the most critical voice in the space is Professor Shelly Palmer.\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 776, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelly Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is the CEO of the Palmer Group and a leading consultant in strategies and solutions for Fortune 500 companies.\", \"from\": 791, \"to\": 904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 812, \"end\": 818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Palmer\", \"score\": 0.9363210018788334, \"rank\": 0.04748479916678517, \"text\": \"Palmer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Palmer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also runs a blog namedShellyPalmer.comin which he wrote a post called, \\\"Why Google'sDear Sydney AdMakes Me Want to Scream.\\\"\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 1032, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the blog post, Professor Shelley explained: \\\"To be clear, I love the idea of a young aspiring athlete inspired by an Olympic athlete.\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1062, \"end\": 1069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\", \"score\": 0.999965524897714, \"rank\": 3.4476290872332087e-05, \"text\": \"Shelley\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's awesome.\\\"\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1187, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, he expressed concern over the intended message of the ad, saying, \\\"This is exactly what we do not want anyone to do with AI.\", \"from\": 1189, \"to\": 1322, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 4.3677762977779635e-12, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ever.\\\"\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Professor Shelley was especially critical of Google's ad, deliberately making \\\"misleading promises of AI's capabilities.\\\"\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1341, \"end\": 1348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\", \"score\": 0.999965524897714, \"rank\": 3.4476290872332087e-05, \"text\": \"Shelley\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\"}, {\"begin\": 1376, \"end\": 1382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9998481937848054, \"rank\": 0.0001518292615539078, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 1433, \"end\": 1435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 4.3677762977779635e-12, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In relation to this concern, Shelley said: \\\"The commercial suggests that a poorly worded prompt, processed by a pattern-matching autocomplete algorithm, can empower an LLM to articulate a person's feelings better than the person themselves.\\\"\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1483, \"end\": 1490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\", \"score\": 0.999965524897714, \"rank\": 3.4476290872332087e-05, \"text\": \"Shelley\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\"}, {\"begin\": 1622, \"end\": 1625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Master_of_Laws\", \"score\": 0.9999999999517968, \"rank\": 4.8155467498264254e-11, \"text\": \"LLM\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Master_of_Laws\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Master_of_Laws\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This once again brings communications experts' concerns over the use of AI for personal tasks such as letter writing to the forefront.\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1769, \"end\": 1771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 4.3677762977779635e-12, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's becoming abundantly clear that AI and, by extension, AI ads are here to stay, and Google is not the first company to face backlash over these ads.\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1869, \"end\": 1871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 4.3677762977779635e-12, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 1891, \"end\": 1893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 4.3677762977779635e-12, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 1920, \"end\": 1926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9998481937848054, \"rank\": 0.0001518292615539078, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It likely will not be the last either.\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In May,Applewas also criticized for a similar ad titled \\\"Crush.\\\"\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2089, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This ad was negatively received because it depicted a hydraulic press crushing various creative tools such as guitars and cameras.\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2220, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ad prompted high-profile creatives, such as Hugh Grant, to label the message of the ad as negative because \\\"it called for the eradication of human creativity.\\\"\", \"from\": 2222, \"to\": 2385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2270, \"end\": 2280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hugh_Grant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8645659942477268e-16, \"text\": \"Hugh Grant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hugh_Grant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hugh_Grant\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the similarities do not stop there.\", \"from\": 2387, \"to\": 2431, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This mounting backlash prompted both Google and Apple to apologize.\", \"from\": 2432, \"to\": 2499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2469, \"end\": 2475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9998481937848054, \"rank\": 0.0001518292615539078, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 2480, \"end\": 2485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5087542339661092e-14, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A spokesman from Google told AdAge that \\\"the company believes AI can be a valuable tool to push human creativity, but it will never replace it.\\\"\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2517, \"end\": 2523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9998481937848054, \"rank\": 0.0001518292615539078, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 2529, \"end\": 2534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ad_Age\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"AdAge\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ad_Age\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ad_Age\"}, {\"begin\": 2562, \"end\": 2564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 4.3677762977779635e-12, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly, in May, Apple also issued a public apology.\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2700, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2665, \"end\": 2670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5087542339661092e-14, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheCaliforniatech giants said the \\\"Crush\\\" ad missed the mark and also reiterated their commitment to celebrating human creativity.\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See all thelatest newsfrom Greece and the world atGreekreporter.com.Contact our newsroomto report an update or send your story, photos and videos.\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2860, \"end\": 2866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9281680518601599, \"rank\": 0.07458400166186482, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow GR onGoogle Newsandsubscribe hereto our daily email!\", \"from\": 2980, \"to\": 3039, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 Copyright - GreekReporter.com\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3072, \"entities\": []}]}"